---
/**
 * CICDSecretsVisual.astro
 * Secrets management in CI/CD pipelines
 */
---

<div class="csv-wrap">
  <h3 class="csv-title">CI/CD Secrets — Safe vs Dangerous Patterns</h3>
  <div class="csv-patterns">
    <div class="csv-section bad">
      <div class="csv-slabel">❌ Anti-Patterns</div>
      <div class="csv-items">
        <div class="csv-item" style="--i:0;">Secrets hardcoded in Dockerfiles or source code</div>
        <div class="csv-item" style="--i:1;">Secrets in environment variables logged to CI output</div>
        <div class="csv-item" style="--i:2;">Shared service accounts with no rotation</div>
        <div class="csv-item" style="--i:3;">Secrets copy-pasted between pipeline configs</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="csv-section good">
      <div class="csv-slabel">✅ Best Practices</div>
      <div class="csv-items">
        <div class="csv-item" style="--i:4;">Pull secrets at runtime from Vault/AWS SM/GCP SM</div>
        <div class="csv-item" style="--i:5;">Short-lived OIDC tokens for cloud auth (no static keys)</div>
        <div class="csv-item" style="--i:6;">Masked/redacted secrets in CI logs automatically</div>
        <div class="csv-item" style="--i:7;">Least-privilege: each pipeline gets only needed secrets</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .csv-wrap{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0f172a,#1e293b);border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:16px;padding:2rem;margin:2rem 0}
  .csv-title{color:#f1f5f9;text-align:center;font-size:1.25rem;margin:0 0 1.5rem}
  .csv-patterns{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(250px,1fr));gap:1rem}
  .csv-section{background:rgba(0,0,0,.2);border-radius:12px;padding:1rem}
  .csv-section.bad{border-top:3px solid #ef4444}
  .csv-section.good{border-top:3px solid #4ade80}
  .csv-slabel{font-weight:700;font-size:.85rem;margin-bottom:.6rem}
  .csv-section.bad .csv-slabel{color:#ef4444}
  .csv-section.good .csv-slabel{color:#4ade80}
  .csv-items{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:.4rem}
  .csv-item{color:#94a3b8;font-size:.73rem;padding:.4rem .6rem;background:rgba(0,0,0,.15);border-radius:6px;opacity:0;animation:csvFade .3s ease forwards;animation-delay:calc(var(--i)*.08s)}
  @keyframes csvFade{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(6px)}to{opacity:1;transform:translateY(0)}}
</style>
